# Terminology

This file defines the documentation language policy and the operating terms used across {{PROJECT_NAME}}. When terminology is uncertain, this file wins.

## 1. Language Policy

- All files under `docs/` are written in {{DOCS_LANG}}.
- Code identifiers, file paths, and metric names stay verbatim in their original form; never translate or paraphrase them.
- Claude Chat replies to {{USER_NAME}} are written in {{CHAT_LANG}} by default, unless {{USER_NAME}} explicitly asks otherwise.
- Claude Code / Codex prompts may be written in {{CODE_LANG}}, but they must preserve the path variables and operational constraints exactly. See `docs/entrypoint.md` section 0 for the canonical path variables.

## 2. Operating Terms

| Term | Meaning |
|---|---|
| {{EXPERIMENT_UNIT_LABEL}} | One controlled unit of work that changes a single component and produces a verdict. The unit of attribution in this framework. |
| {{ANALYSIS_RECORD_LABEL}} | A durable record that groups related {{EXPERIMENT_UNIT_LABEL}}s and their conclusions; indexed in `docs/project/themes/theme-index.md`. |
| operation modes | The way every request is classified: six lifecycle modes (Investigate, Design, Implement, Experiment, Analyze, Write) plus two cross-cutting modes (Auto, Maintain). Defined in `docs/operations/operation-modes.md`. |
| SRC | A source-code change (the work of Implement mode): editing the project code so a {{EXPERIMENT_UNIT_LABEL}} can be run. Distinct from running it. |
| RUN | Executing prepared code to produce results (the work of Experiment mode). SRC lands first, then RUN; a verdict needs RUN output. |
| Analyze (analysis mode) | The read-only mode that draws conclusions from the project's own artifacts and critically verifies them; protocol in `docs/operations/analysis-mode.md`. |
| Maintain (maintenance mode) | The cross-cutting mode for docs consistency, large-scale cleanup, and the reflection ritual; protocol in `docs/operations/maintenance-mode.md`. |
<!-- if:ENABLE_AUTO_MODE=yes -->| Auto (auto mode) | The cross-cutting mode that autonomously chains lifecycle modes within hard safety boundaries; protocol in `docs/operations/auto-mode.md`. |<!-- endif -->
| Project Instructions | The pasteable instruction block {{USER_NAME}} installs into Claude Chat; mastered in `docs/operations/project-memory-and-instructions.md` section 2. The {{ROLE_TERM}} never edits it silently. |
| verdict | The outcome label assigned to a {{EXPERIMENT_UNIT_LABEL}} by Analyze or Experiment; the vocabulary is defined in `docs/evaluation/evaluation-and-visualization.md` section 2. |

